                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/336.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                        General <persName type="to">Goding</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-12T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 12, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Forward following to Agent, Esmeraldas: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Your undated telegram. Report briefly by cable effects of bombardment if
                            such has occurred. You will use your good offices between the two
                            combatant forces to endeavor to secure establishment of a neutral zone
                            where non-combatants may be out of danger.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>No warship available at present.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
